source: TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_ASK_DISPOSE<tab>Are you certain you wish to remove this crop?
TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_TALK_FLOWER_VIGOROUS<tab>The <var 2F ((<var 28 ((Item)) E8020A /var>)) /var> have taken root, and the crop is doing well.
target: TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_TALK_FLOWER_VIGOROUS<tab>In diesem Blumentopf wächst eine Pflanze. Sie gedeiht prächtig. (<var 2B ((<var 28 ((Item)) E8020A /var>)) /var>)

source: TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_TALK_FLOWER_DEPRESSED<tab>The <var 2F ((<var 28 ((Item)) E8020A /var>)) /var> have taken root, but the crop has seen better days...

source: TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_FLOWER_PREDICT<tab>Perhaps it will yield <var 09 E802 ((red flowers)) ((blue flowers)) ((yellow flowers)) ((green flowers)) ((orange flowers)) ((purple flowers)) ((flowers, but who can say what color they might be)) /var>...
target: TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_FLOWER_PREDICT<tab>Die Pflanze wird bald <var 09 E802 ((rot)) ((blau)) ((gelb)) ((grün)) ((orange)) ((violett)) ((in einer schönen Farbe)) /var> blühen.

source: TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_FLOWER_PREDICT_UNKNOWN<tab>Perhaps it will yield <var 09 E802 ((red)) ((blue)) ((yellow)) ((green)) ((orange)) ((purple)) /var> flowers, or perhaps flowers of a more unusual shade...
target: TEXT_HOUFURPLANTPOT_00331_FLOWER_PREDICT_UNKNOWN<tab>Die Pflanze wird bald <var 09 E802 ((rot)) ((blau)) ((gelb)) ((grün)) ((orange)) ((violett)) /var> oder in einer ganz besonderen Farbe blühen.
